    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Adding `SafeFuture` has turned out to be one of the best decisions we've made in Teku. It's grown quite a few really useful utility methods to make working with futures easier and fixed a *lot* of places where we would have lost exceptions.\r\n\r\nThere has been almost no cost to using it because you can pass a `SafeFuture` to anything that wants a `CompletableFuture` and anything that returns a `CompletableFuture` can easily be converted with `SafeFuture.of(CompletableFuture)`.",
